Bun makes it fast to work with SQLite and S3 right out of the box––no extra npm packages needed.

Spin up a Supabase project free at [database.new](https://database.new). You’ll get Postgres and S3 storage instantly.

Just drop in your Supabase env variables:

```bash
SUPABASE_URL=<your-supabase-url>
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<your-anon-key>
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<service-role-key>
SUPABASE_S3_URL=<supabase-s3-url>
SUPABASE_S3_KEY=<s3-key>
SUPABASE_S3_SECRET=<s3-secret>
```

Now, uploading a file to S3 or querying Postgres with Bun looks like:

```js
// Upload
await Bun.S3.put('folder/file.txt', fileBuffer, { 
  bucket: process.env.SUPABASE_S3_URL, 
  accessKey: process.env.SUPABASE_S3_KEY, 
  secretKey: process.env.SUPABASE_S3_SECRET 
});
// Query
const db = Bun.postgres(process.env.SUPABASE_URL, { password: process.env.SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY });
const rows = await db.query("SELECT * FROM my_table");
```

Less setup, less code, faster ops—and easy to hand off if you’re using AI coding assistants later.